his self-confidence,

00:10:43.440 --> 00:10:45.570 align:middle line:90%
his self-image.

00:10:45.570 --> 00:10:50.850 align:middle line:84%
He stayed home every day and
drank and smoked and cursed

00:10:50.850 --> 00:10:55.080 align:middle line:84%
and burped and whatever
around us children,

00:10:55.080 --> 00:10:57.000 align:middle line:90%
while my mother went to work.

00:10:57.000 --> 00:11:00.360 align:middle line:84%
Six people on a bank
teller's salary.

00:11:00.360 --> 00:11:04.740 align:middle line:84%
So needless to say, our
lives were rather meager.

00:11:04.740 --> 00:11:07.230 align:middle line:84%
My parents really
didn't have friends.

00:11:07.230 --> 00:11:09.570 align:middle line:84%
They didn't have other
people they spent time with.

00:11:09.570 --> 00:11:12.930 align:middle line:84%
It was just the family and
work or whatever for my mom,

00:11:12.930 --> 00:11:14.730 align:middle line:90%
and church.

00:11:14.730 --> 00:11:18.360 align:middle line:84%
Church was more important
than anything to her,

00:11:18.360 --> 00:11:22.140 align:middle line:84%
it appeared, from
my perspective.

00:11:22.140 --> 00:11:26.130 align:middle line:84%
When I went to her for
advice when I was younger,

00:11:26.130 --> 00:11:29.535 align:middle line:84%
