00:11:36.900 --> 00:11:41.040 align:middle line:84%
He began to develop a drinking
problem at that young age.

00:11:41.040 --> 00:11:45.060 align:middle line:84%
And with time,
full-blown alcoholism.

00:11:45.060 --> 00:11:50.140 align:middle line:84%
After he lost his job,
he became very violent.

00:11:50.140 --> 00:11:53.100 align:middle line:84%
My mother would often go
to work with black eyes.

00:11:53.100 --> 00:11:55.620 align:middle line:84%
She would try to make
up excuses for him

00:11:55.620 --> 00:11:58.650 align:middle line:84%
like my little brother jabbed
her in the eye or something

00:11:58.650 --> 00:12:03.720 align:middle line:84%
when he was in bed with her,
something to protect my father.

00:12:03.720 --> 00:12:05.700 align:middle line:84%
And with the rest
of us children,

00:12:05.700 --> 00:12:10.500 align:middle line:84%
we learned to walk on eggshells
as we grew up because he

00:12:10.500 --> 00:12:11.940 align:middle line:90%
was very, very volatile.

00:12:11.940 --> 00:12:15.480 align:middle line:84%
He could fly off and send
someone flying across the room

00:12:15.480 --> 00:12:17.625 align:middle line:84%
or hit your head so
hard you saw stars.

00:12:17.625 --> 00:12:20.390 align:middle line:90%


00:12:20.390 --> 00:12:24.750 align:middle line:84%
One of my worst memories
was watching my father

00:12:24.750 --> 00:12:28.880 align:middle line:84%
take a hairbrush to my little
brother who was about 4 or 5

00:12:28.880 --> 00:12:33.320 align:middle line:84%
at the time and
just systematically

00:12:33.320 --> 00:12:36.620 align:middle line:84%
beating his little head
as hard as he could with--

00:12:36.620 --> 00:12:38.630 align:middle line:84%
I mean, it was abuse
with the hairbrush

00:12:38.630 --> 00:12:42.980 align:middle line:84%
so that he had a little
crewcut at the time

00:12:42.980 --> 00:12:49.100 align:middle line:84%
and there were raised black and
blue welts all over his head.

00:12:49.100 --> 00:12:51.560 align:middle line:84%
His offense was my
little sister was

00:12:51.560 --> 00:12:54.080 align:middle line:84%
crying so he was going
to punish my brother,

00:12:54.080 --> 00:12:56.780 align:middle line:84%
if that makes sense,
that's what happened.

00:12:56.780 --> 00:12:58.760 align:middle line:84%
When my mother came
home from work,

00:12:58.760 --> 00:13:01.970 align:middle line:84%
I still remember her saying,
"oh, John," my father's name

00:13:01.970 --> 00:13:04.340 align:middle line:84%
was John, "you shouldn't
do that to the children,"

00:13:04.340 --> 00:13:06.950 align:middle line:90%
and that was it.

00:13:06.950 --> 00:13:09.350 align:middle line:84%
There was an
unwritten rule where

00:13:09.350 --> 00:13:12.485 align:middle line:84%
you don't talk about what
goes on in the house.

00:13:12.485 --> 00:13:15.750 align:middle line:90%
You don't share what goes on.

00:13:15.750 --> 00:13:18.020 align:middle line:84%
And so in the
outside world, we'd

00:13:18.020 --> 00:13:22.650 align:middle line:84%
look like a normal happy family,
pretty much, but inwardly,

00:13:22.650 --> 00:13:26.090 align:middle line:90%
it was anything but.

00:13:26.090 --> 00:13:31.425 align:middle line:84%
By age 9, sexual
abuse began with me.

00:13:31.425 --> 00:13:34.660 align:middle line:90%


00:13:34.660 --> 00:13:41.680 align:middle line:84%
After he was finished with
me, he pushed me off the sofa,

00:13:41.680 --> 00:13:45.580 align:middle line:84%
I remember, and
said, "now, go play."

00:13:45.580 --> 00:13:49.280 align:middle line:84%
About age 10, abuse
was almost daily.

00:13:49.280 --> 00:13:53.080 align:middle line:84%
So I would find a way, I'd
maybe just run outside and play

00:13:53.080 --> 00:13:56.140 align:middle line:84%
or whatever I could
to get away from him.

00:13:56.140 --> 00:13:58.390 align:middle line:90%
And I finally did tell my mom.

00:13:58.390 --> 00:14:03.340 align:middle line:84%
She said, "well, honey, daddy's
just trying to help you."

00:14:03.340 --> 00:14:05.410 align:middle line:90%
And that was it.

00:14:05.410 --> 00:14:09.420 align:middle line:84%
And my thought was,
"help me what?"

00:14:09.420 --> 00:14:13.710 align:middle line:10%
In the summers at my
grandparents' house in Idaho,

00:14:13.710 --> 00:14:15.460 align:middle line:10%
I didn't have to cope.

00:14:15.460 --> 00:14:20.160 align:middle line:10%
I played and swam and fished
and ran and hiked and did

00:14:20.160 --> 00:14:22.815 align:middle line:10%
everything my tomboy
heart desired.

00:14:22.815 --> 00:14:27.360 align:middle line:90%


00:14:27.360 --> 00:14:31.380 align:middle line:84%
There was a big ponderosa pine
at the beginning of the trail

00:14:31.380 --> 00:14:33.600 align:middle line:90%
leading down to the lake.

00:14:33.600 --> 00:14:38.664 align:middle line:84%
And I could sit under that
what I called my thinking tree.

00:14:38.664 --> 00:14:41.049 align:middle line:90%
